rComments: Prof. Stickle is the best professor I've ever met. His unique way of teaching is not too pressing but it is very educative.
Very understanding and a very clear lecturer, he should teach other first year engineering courses, i would love to have him as a professor again
Very easy-going with the lectures and tutorials. You still need to put effort on assignments though for APS100!
Best Prof ever had
BEST PROF EVER.

I really enjoyed having him as a prof for this course. The "inverted classroom" approach really helped me since I tend to learn better in lectures when I've read the material beforehand. His tests are tough but fair. He's a great lecturer and really cares about his students. He's also pretty cute.
Good teacher. He really cares about electromagnetics. Very understanding and tries his best to make every learn and do well in the course. I don't like his inverted classroom idea too much though
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Respected', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: God of lecturers. He follows one simple rule: teach you everything, test you everything that is taught. This is very simple. His course is tough precisely because he tests everything that is taught, no more, no less. Other professors tests what is not taught, or teach stuff not tested - just awful. Stickel should show them how it is done.
Very helpful guy. Interesting lectures with lots of real life examples. Gives a lot of practice problems and tests so make use of his material. Don't be afraid to talk to him if you have a problem
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: He's ok. Not as good as everyone says
genius prof and nice lectures :D we were scared of his exams but he gave good bell curves and super helpful review sessions!

Very hard course, however one of the best professors you will ever have, certainly was for me so far. He will help you and is very patient. If you try and follow him, you will succeed, but don't expect to fly by, he makes sure you understand the material. He provides you with everything necessary and more to learn effectively.
Great guy!

Great prof who really does care about his students. He puts in the time to make the videos and he tries to answer everyone's questions. However, he is as hard as everyone says he is so study hard! Also, make sure to do well on all the extra little things he has because those marks add up!

Didn't do well but I can only blame myself for attempting a high-school approach to studying for his tests, which absolutely demand that you know the fundamentals and not how to plug in formulas. Stickel gave me a good wake-up call about my study habits. Wasn't pretty for my GPA but I am nevertheless grateful for being pushed to improve myself.

Stickel is good at teaching. Like everyone else said, understanding key concepts is really the most fundamental! Try his example problems on portal, try every single Q of them, it did help quite a lot. Watch his videos, go to lectures, do problems, review 15-30mins before tutorial, believe me, you are gonna ACE it easily!

This class is about understanding the concept. I did very well on the midterm(got 98%),which lots of people failed, and the class average was about 57%, but I didn't try any question and past exam at all. All I did was reviewing his lecture video. Many people I know just memorizing the solution steps without understanding, so they did pretty bad.
he seems so sad sometimes i just want to give him a nice big hug :))))))

Pretty good prof, but his "inverted classroom" approach is horrible. He basically tries to get you to spend 5 times as long studying his subject than your other subjects. And then he's so confident that it's making you an EM genius that he gives extremely hard exams. Good guy who knows his stuff though, and his lectures are enjoyable.

He implemented a so called inverted classroom, which is extremely bad. We basically have to study all of the material on our own. I mean what's the point to do that, if there has already been excellent online resources, such as mit ocw. He lacks insight to E&M, just to give extremely complicated number to calculated in the test.
Very hard working and organised.  Has a lot of sources and teaches very clearly. Also talks about related stuff outside of course. Overall a very good prof.
People seem to struggle in this course, but it's actually not that hard once you get the concept. The explanation is crystally clear. Lots of online resources. Great experience in this class!

Man this guy is a genius. I think his name shouldn't be here cos if you are an ECE student you must cross his part before you get in to 3ed year. So like it or not you better know the subject inside out cos exams are extremely hard. There is no easy, median then hard questions in his exams. it just brain killers. But you will love his class.
very good. doesnt speak clearly. very hard marker.

Amazing lecturer, really hard tests. Presents material more clearly then any other professor I have seen and I've had civ102 with collins :D. Very friendly, very helpful. His lectures are easily the best of 2nd year first term (although all profs I have this term are pretty solid)
I personally don't like him but he's a great guy. He's devoted to teaching those who are willing to learn. Loves using hand gestures. Tricky to understand at times.
Very nice guy. Helpful in office hours. Course itself is very hard and he tries to make it easier. Doesn't do the greatest job there, but still a nice guy.
